    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>This plugin may be helpful if you sale your products in both WooCommerce and Allegro. It can sync the products&#8217; quantity between your online stores when client buys a product.</p>\n",
        "faq": "\n<h4>\nHow to configure the plugin?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>You can get access to the configuration panel under <code>Tools -&gt; Integration of Allegro and WooCommerce</code> in your WordPress panel.</p>\n</p>\n<h4>\nHow to link to Allegro?\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>This process is well described in the config panel. On <a href=\"https://github.com/dotandl/integration-allegro-woocommerce\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">GitHub</a> you can also find some help.</p>\n</p>\n<h4>\nI&#8217;ve found a bug/I&#8217;d like to improve the plugin\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Open new GitHub Issue or PR in the <a href=\"https://github.com/dotandl/integration-allegro-woocommerce\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">project&#8217;s repository</a></p>\n</p>\n\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>1.0.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>First version of the plugin</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>1.0.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix some problems that may make the plugin not work</li>\n<li>Fix the bug that Allegro API Token refreshes twice and the second refresh makes HTTP 400 error</li>\n</ul>\n"
    },
